# [Wikipedia:Manual of Style/Formatting text for people with disabilities](/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style/Formatting_text_for_people_with_disabilities)

This page is a [redirect](/Wikipedia:Redirect). The following [categories](/Wikipedia:Categorizing_redirects) are used to track and monitor this redirect:

## Redirect Classification

This redirect falls into multiple tracking categories, because apparently one classification wasn't sufficiently bureaucratic:

• **[From a page move](/Category:Redirects_from_moves)**: This is a redirect from a page that has been moved (renamed). This page was kept as a redirect to avoid breaking links, both internal and external, that may have been made to the old page name. Because nothing says "evolved information architecture" like leaving digital breadcrumbs everywhere.

• **[To a project page](/Category:Redirects_to_project_page)**: This is a redirect from any page inside or outside of [project (Wikipedia: or WP:) space](/Wikipedia:Project_namespace) to any page within the project [namespace](/Wikipedia:Namespace) ( not to a project talk page ). The above category link leads to a list of redirects from inside project space. Redirects from outside project space are automatically sorted to [Category:Redirects to project namespace](/Category:Redirects_to_project_namespace). Because categorization is apparently an art form best practiced with maximum complexity.

• **[To a subpage](/Category:Redirects_to_subpages)**: This is a redirect to a subpage. In a page title, a [subpage](/Wikipedia:Subpages) name appears after a [forward slash](/Slash_(punctuation)) (/); for example, "Wikipedia:Technical move requests" redirects to [Wikipedia:Requested moves/Technical requests](/Wikipedia:Requested_moves/Technical_requests), which is a subpage of [Wikipedia:Requested moves](/Wikipedia:Requested_moves). Please note that not every page title with "/" in its title is a subpage. See this template's [documentation](/Template:R_to_subpage/doc) for details. Because naturally there are exceptions to subpage identification—because why make anything straightforward?

• **[From a shortcut](/Category:Redirects_from_shortcuts)**: This is a redirect from a [shortcut](/Wikipedia:Shortcut) in any namespace to a page in any namespace. Shortcuts are [wikilinked](/Wikilink) on community pages, talk pages, and edit summaries, but not in [mainspace](/Wikipedia:Mainspace) articles. Because consistency in linking conventions would be too pedestrian, apparently.

## Protection and Maintenance

When appropriate, [protection levels](/Wikipedia:Protection_policy) are automatically sensed, described and categorized. Because nothing says "robust infrastructure" like automated protection level detection—as if the page itself has opinions about who should be allowed to touch it.

